{"doc":{"isMarkdown":true,"isTranslated":false,"isActive":true,"flaws":{},"title":"VideoFrame.allocationSize()","mdn_url":"/en-US/docs/Web/API/VideoFrame/allocationSize","locale":"en-US","native":"English (US)","sidebarHTML":"","body":[{"type":"prose","value":{"id":null,"title":null,"isH3":false,"content":"<p>The <strong><code>allocationSize()</code></strong> method of the <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/VideoFrame\"><code>VideoFrame</code></a> interface returns the number of bytes required to hold the video as filtered by options passed into the method.</p>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"syntax","title":"Syntax","isH3":false,"content":"<div class=\"code-example\"><pre class=\"brush: js notranslate\"><code>VideoFrame<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">allocationSize</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\nVideoFrame<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">allocationSize</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>options<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n</code></pre></div>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"parameters","title":"Parameters","isH3":true,"content":"<dl>\n  <dt id=\"options\"><code>options</code><span class=\"badge inline optional\">Optional</span></dt>\n  <dd>\n    <p>An object containing the following:</p>\n    <dl>\n      <dt id=\"rect\"><code>rect</code><span class=\"badge inline optional\">Optional</span></dt>\n      <dd>\n        <p>The rectangle of pixels to copy from the <code>VideoFrame</code>. If unspecified the <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/VideoFrame/visibleRect\" title=\"visibleRect\"><code>visibleRect</code></a> will be used. This is in the format of a dictionary object containing:</p>\n        <ul>\n          <li><code>x</code>: The x-coordinate.</li>\n          <li><code>y</code>: The y-coordinate.</li>\n          <li><code>width</code>: The width of the frame.</li>\n          <li><code>height</code>: The height of the frame.</li>\n        </ul>\n      </dd>\n      <dt id=\"layout\"><code>layout</code><span class=\"badge inline optional\">Optional</span></dt>\n      <dd>\n        <p>A list containing the following values for each plane in the <code>VideoFrame</code>. Planes may not overlap. If unspecified the planes will be tightly packed:</p>\n        <ul>\n          <li><code>offset</code>: An integer representing the offset in bytes where the given plane begins.</li>\n          <li><code>stride</code>: An integer representing the number of bytes, including padding, used by each row of the plane.</li>\n        </ul>\n      </dd>\n    </dl>\n  </dd>\n</dl>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"return_value","title":"Return Value","isH3":true,"content":"<p>An integer containing the number of bytes needed to hold the frame as specified by <code>options</code>.</p>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"examples","title":"Examples","isH3":false,"content":"<p>In the following example the <code>allocationSize</code> is returned for the rectangle at top left with dimensions of 800 by 600.</p>\n<div class=\"code-example\"><pre class=\"brush: js notranslate\"><code><span class=\"token keyword\">const</span> videoRect <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n  <span class=\"token literal-property property\">x</span><span class=\"token operator\">:</span><span class=\"token number\">0</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n  <span class=\"token literal-property property\">y</span><span class=\"token operator\">:</span><span class=\"token number\">0</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n  <span class=\"token literal-property property\">width</span><span class=\"token operator\">:</span><span class=\"token number\">800</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n  <span class=\"token literal-property property\">height</span><span class=\"token operator\">:</span><span class=\"token number\">600</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n<span class=\"token keyword\">let</span> size <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> VideoFrame<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">allocationSize</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span><span class=\"token literal-property property\">rect</span><span class=\"token operator\">:</span> videoRect<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span>\n</code></pre></div>"}},{"type":"specifications","value":{"title":"Specifications","id":"specifications","isH3":false,"specifications":[{"bcdSpecificationURL":"https://w3c.github.io/webcodecs/#dom-videoframe-allocationsize","title":"WebCodecs"}],"query":"api.VideoFrame.allocationSize"}},{"type":"browser_compatibility","value":{"title":"Browser compatibility","id":"browser_compatibility","isH3":false,"query":"api.VideoFrame.allocationSize","dataURL":"/en-US/docs/Web/API/VideoFrame/allocationSize/bcd.json"}}],"toc":[{"text":"Syntax","id":"syntax"},{"text":"Examples","id":"examples"},{"text":"Specifications","id":"specifications"},{"text":"Browser compatibility","id":"browser_compatibility"}],"summary":"The allocationSize() method of the VideoFrame interface returns the number of bytes required to hold the video as filtered by options passed into the method.","popularity":0,"modified":"2022-02-04T07:16:02.000Z","source":{"folder":"en-us/web/api/videoframe/allocationsize","github_url":"https://github.com/mdn/content/blob/style/old/files/en-us/web/api/videoframe/allocationsize/index.md","last_commit_url":"https://github.com/mdn/content/commit/614cd623fac41cbc68c54ef33b82dd4d5ebb04f7","filename":"index.md"},"parents":[{"uri":"/en-US/docs/Web","title":"Web technology for developers"},{"uri":"/en-US/docs/Web/API","title":"Web APIs"},{"uri":"/en-US/docs/Web/API/VideoFrame","title":"VideoFrame"},{"uri":"